⚡ High-Speed Perpetual Data Pipeline & Automated Digit Momentum Engine
An enterprise-grade, high-fidelity hybrid trading dashboard designed specifically for trading Over/Under Digit Contracts on the Deriv platform (Volatility 75 Index - R_75).

This platform operates via a completely decoupled data pipeline architecture. The WebSocket data stream and tracking matrix connect and update the millisecond the server boots up, ensuring flawless data flow and 100% availability for Manual Trading Execution even when the automated bot core is disarmed.

## System Architecture: What It Is
The system is built on a Node.js/Express backend and a lightweight, zero-dependency vanilla UI frontend. It communicates with Deriv via direct, low-latency persistent WebSockets (ws), passing data down to the frontend using highly efficient Server-Sent Events (SSE).

Unlike standard bots that pause or crash when connection issues occur, this system utilizes an Automated Background Recovery Bridge that auto-heals and resynchronizes balance telemetry within 1,500 milliseconds of any network disruption.

## Core Strategy Logic: What It Does
The core engine records and analyzes a rolling history array of exactly 100 ticks. Each tick is stripped down to its terminal digit based on asset decimal precision.

### 1. Class-A Saturation Matrix (The Circles)
The engine monitors the distribution percentage of digits 0 through 9:

Green Circle: The mathematical Mode (the single most frequently occurring digit in the last 100 ticks).

Red Circle: The single least frequently occurring digit in the last 100 ticks.

### 2. The Multi-Tier Spatial Filter (Bottleneck 1 Fix)
The system evaluates market structure by validating both density and circle boundaries:

Win-Space Density: The percentage of digits greater than 3 (digits 4 to 9) must be 60% or higher across the entire 100-tick array.

Expanded Boundary Floor: The Red Circle must hold a value of 3, 4, 5, or 6.

Spatial Separation: The gap between the Green Circle and Red Circle (Green - Red) must be less than or equal to 2 (e.g., perfectly qualifying high-performing market profiles like Red=6 / Green=8, Red=4 / Green=5, or Red=3 / Green=4).

### 3. Sequential Momentum Trigger Matrix (Bottleneck 3 Fix)
To achieve precise entry timing, the automated execution loop tracks the sequence of incoming digits:

Defensive Floor Check: The engine waits until a trailing digit prints inside the defensive lower range (0, 1, 2, or 3).

Breakout Blast: The exact millisecond the very next live digit steps up and touches the Red Circle or hits an open integer directly in front of it (within the space up to Green - 1), the system triggers a 1-tick contract via the API.

### 4. Dynamic Capital Preservation Matrix
Auto-Risk Allocation: Both manual and automated execution models automatically calculate a 1% stake based on your real-time wallet balance, complete with a platform floor limit of $0.35.

Daily Target Guardrails: The backend locks down trading operations automatically upon hitting a 2% daily profit target or a 4% max loss ceiling.

3-Tick Settlement Lockout: Toggles a safety block on execution threads immediately upon trade placement to prevent overlapping signals.

10-Tick Rest Window: Enforces a clean post-trade cooldown to avoid choppy market conditions.

## Global Deployment Blueprints: How to Run It
🛠 Required Environment Variables
Every platform requires these two environment variables to establish a secure handshake with the API:

DERIV_APP_ID: Your registered Deriv Application ID.

DERIV_PAT: Your secure Deriv Personal Access Token.

💻 1. VPS Deployment (Ubuntu / Debian)
Best choice for minimum latency. Run this via terminal connection:

Bash


# 1. Update system repositories and install Node.js engine
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs git

# 2. Clone repository and install high-speed dependency tree
git clone <your-repository-url> trading-deck && cd trading-deck
npm install

# 3. Configure Global Production Process Manager
sudo npm install pm2 -g

# 4. Inject Environment Credentials and Initialize
export DERIV_APP_ID="your_app_id_here"
export DERIV_PAT="your_token_here"
pm2 start server.js --name "deriv-deck"

# 5. Set up automatic process recovery on system reboot
pm2 startup && pm2 save
🚀 2. Koyeb Deployment
Sign in to your Koyeb Dashboard and click Create Service.

Select GitHub as the deployment method and authorize your repository.

In the Environment Variables section, add your credentials:

DERIV_APP_ID = [Your Value]

DERIV_PAT = [Your Value]

Set the Exposed Port configuration box to match port 3000.

Click Deploy. Koyeb will automatically parse the workspace and provision a public URL.

🚄 3. Railway Deployment
Open the Railway Console, select New Project, and choose Deploy from GitHub repo.

Once the project initializes, navigate to the Variables tab.

Click New Variable to insert:

DERIV_APP_ID

DERIV_PAT

Railway reads the package.json setup, automatically provisions a standard production PORT variable, and starts running immediately.

🎨 4. Render Deployment
Access the Render Dashboard, click New +, and select Web Service.

Connect your project's GitHub repository.

Configure the following build parameters:

Runtime: Node

Build Command: npm install

Start Command: node server.js

Click the Advanced drop-down menu, choose Add Environment Variable, and provide your DERIV_APP_ID and DERIV_PAT.

Click Deploy Web Service.

🌀 5. Replit Deployment
Create a new Repl container and select Node.js as the base template.

Use the workspace file tree uploader to drop the codebase into the project space.

Open the Secrets (Tools -> Secrets) configuration panel in the left sidebar.

Input your DERIV_APP_ID and DERIV_PAT as key-value pairs.

Click the green Run button at the top of the interface. Replit will install the required dependencies and spin up an integrated web viewer pane.

